718859f-a.text:
Church Street, west side, at Fulton Street.
April 1, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
718859f-a.folder: Church Street & Fulton Street, Manhattan, NY

719964f-b.text:
(1)
Fulton Street, north side, west from but not including Church, to and including West Streets. The 6 story buildings to the right center (triangular cornice) are Trinity Mission (No. 211) and St. Christopher
Chapel (No. 213).
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPROOUCTIONS.  August 6, 1930
(2)
The same view from Church Street. (Sixth Avenue "El" overhead, demolished Spring 1939), showing in the center of this block the demolition of No's 201-3, the Lilly Building. In the foreground, adjoining the corner is Hook and Ladder No. 10. The 2 story structure at the corner (Nedicks) stands on the site of a former 5 story building (No. 191 Fulton Street) which was demolished when Church Street was widened during the construction period of the Municipal (Eighth Avenue) subway. At the left appears Pier 14, occupied by the Fall River Line, and the 1 story Glackner Building. The latter bears No's. 192 Greenwich Street and 227-229 Fulton Street and stands at the N.W. corner.Obscuring
the lover portion of these is the Ninth Avenue "E1".
August 2, 1938
P. L. Sperr.
